      "message": "validation: merge `PeekCoin` into `GetCoin`\n\nMerge `PeekCoin` into `GetCoin` by adding a `peek_only` flag to the `CCoinsView` interface and removing the separate virtual method.\nThis keeps the non-caching lookup behavior for `CCoinsViewCache` and `CoinsViewOverlay`, while letting backends without caches ignore the flag.\n\nTests and fuzz scaffolding now call `GetCoin(..., true)` directly where the non-caching behavior matters, and `CCoinsViewCache` shares the common result handling between peeking and caching lookups.\nOnly the call sites that need side-effect-free reads keep `GetCoin(..., true)`, the post-`Flush()` overlay assertions can use plain `GetCoin()` because they only check the flushed spentness and do not need to preserve parent cache state.\n\nThis simplification was suggested by:\n* Rus Yanofsky in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34165#pullrequestreview-3828444258\n* Anthony Towns in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34124#issuecomment-4037752227\n\nCo-authored-by: ryanofsky <ryan@ofsky.org>\nCo-authored-by: Anthony Towns <aj@erisian.com.au>",
